# 13 Towers of Hell — Architecture Rules

## Monorepo Structure
- `packages/shared-types/` — Shared TypeScript interfaces (PlayerState, Web3 payloads, AI responses)
- `packages/game-config/` — Global constants (Floor data, Item IDs, Z-order index)
- `apps/client/` — Frontend & game engine (Vite + TypeScript canvas)
- `apps/backend/` — Backend API (Next.js)
- `apps/ai-agents/` — AI agent microservice (Node.js)
- `apps/contracts/` — Smart contracts (Foundry / Solidity, Monad EVM)

## Conventions
- All new code must match existing style (no comments, monospace font, silhouette aesthetic)
- Imports: use relative paths within the same app; use workspace references for shared packages
- Contracts: Solidity 0.8.27, Cancun EVM, via-ir optimizer
- Client: 2D canvas engine (entities under engine/, rendering under engine/rendering/)
